According to statistics, between 30 and 75 % of road users accused more than once of driving drunk again in this condition will sit behind the wheel.
Alcolock should prevent this because it is a system connected to a vehicle that measures the level of alcohol in the breathed air and prevents the car from starting if the driver does not breathe before or if it is recorded above the permitted concentration of alcohol.
Its price exceeds 1,000 euros and would have to be paid by the culprit himself.
The study carried out in this sense in the USA in 2007 showed that in the case of vehicles equipped with this equipment, the infringements decreased by 65 % during the first year following the introduction.
In Spain it is calculated that it could save 115 lives each year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: that such behaviour should be dealt with before it commits a criminal offence.
And in order to assist in its implementation, since legislation can be implemented in the usual way, the necessary adjustment of criminal provisions requires a change in the law.
The equipment is not yet available on the Spanish market in any sales version, although some industrial cars and public service vehicles have already been installed.
